==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Dandie Dinmont
<hw>Dan"die Din"mont</hw> }</mhw>,
<pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In Scott's ⟦ldquo⟧Guy Mannering⟦rdquo⟧, a
Border farmer of eccentric but fine character, who owns two terriers
claimed to be the progenitors of the Dandie Dinmont terriers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of a breed of terriers with short legs, long
body, and rough coat, originating in the country about the English and
Scotch border.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dandified</ent>⟦br⟧
